==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wadding
<hw>Wad"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Wad</er> a
little mass.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A wad, or the materials for wads; any pliable
substance of which wads may be made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any soft stuff of loose texture, used for stuffing
or padding garments; esp., sheets of carded cotton prepared for the
purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waddle</ent>⟦br⟧
